<div class="container">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div id="comments-1">
        
            <article id="comment-953">
              <time datetime="2011-09-12">September 12, 2011</time>
              <p>I visited Busaba / Bicester Village on Saturday 10th September. My wife had the Pad Thai which she said was delicious and I had the Black Pepper Beef which was divine, and the Goong Tohd Prawns which were wonderful. The restaurant was stylish, clean and the service was excellent. If I had to be picky I would have liked a slightly larger portion, but then again i'm 6'4 and 16 stone so eat more than most!</p>
              <p class="author">From Stewart Garrard</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-949">
              <time datetime="2011-09-10">September 10, 2011</time>
              <p>Walking Around Westfieds starving. Hearing my friend going on and on about this Lychee and lamb curry , i started to feel intrigued.  Curiosity got the better of me.
<br /> Upon arriving u are immediately hit with this intense feeling of calmness but yet a buzzing atmosphere, The subtle yet effective lighting prepares your mind and body for the ultimate eating experience. 
<br />The service was polite and efficient with a great knowledge of the dishes and ingredients. 
<br />so decided to try this lychee and lamb curry. one Word, WOW. such an understanding of flavours that balance perfectly on the palette.  Felt so satisfied and glad i had this experience. my aim is to go as many times as possible to sample all the great dishes on offer.
<br /> The downside for me was the sharing of the tables it can be a bit encroaching on ones personal space, however after a while its barely noticeable. another minus is the lack of desserts. l love to have something sweet especially after something spicy. I have read other reviews which mention the long waiting times. luckily i did not experience that. In my mind the fact there are queues is a testament to how great this dinning experience truly is.</p>
              <p class="author">From Nina West London</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-933">
              <time datetime="2011-08-22">August 22, 2011</time>
              <p>Came to Busabu on Saturday night with a large group of 8, and despite being very busy they found room for us all and were very polite and the food was very fast in coming. It tasted amazing, excellent quality for such a reasonable price considering the locale. I honestly am looking forward to my next trip. Be prepared for a queue if you leave it too late though, this place is very popular for obvious reasons!</p>
              <p class="author">From LondonHyena</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-929">
              <time datetime="2011-08-18">August 18, 2011</time>
              <p>While visiting London last week we were told to go to this Thai Restaurant just up the road from our hotel. It was the best thing we did in London. The food was absolutely divine. The first night we had Pad Thai, Duck curry and rice.yummy. It was so good that we decided to go back the next night. We had Pad Thai,Chicken and butternut squash,Chinese broccoli and coconut rice.OMG I didn't want to leave anything on my plate it was that nice. I'd go back to London just to eat there</p>
              <p class="author">From Shere</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-925">
              <time datetime="2011-08-15">August 15, 2011</time>
              <p>Visited Busaba this past saturday. Wonderful food. The &quot;calamari&quot; was simply delicious (and this is an assessment from someone who does not really like calamari).</p>

<p>I would recommend this place without an ounce of reservation!</p>
              <p class="author">From Chris</p>
    
            </article>

